definition.value: A sulfinic acid derivative obtained by formal condensation of propanethiosulfinic acid with propanethiol.
A benzochromenone that is beta-lapachone in which one of the hydrogens attached to the carbon adjacent to that bearing the gem-dimethyls is replaced by a bromine.
A triterpenoid saponin that is cycloastragenol glycosylated at positions 3 and 6 by 2,3-di-O-acetyl-beta-D-xylosyl and beta-D-glucosyl residues respectively.
Any inhibitor of erythropoietin, a glycoprotein hormone that controls erythropoiesis (red blood cell production).
A triterpenoid saponin that is cycloastragenol glycosylated at positions 3 and 6 by 2-O-acetyl-beta-D-xylosyl and beta-D-glucosyl residues respectively.
A hydrochloride obtained by combining biliverdin with one molar equivalent of hydrogen chloride.
An organic sodium salt that is the monosodium salt of dehydroepiandrosterone sulfate.
A pyrimidinecarboxylate ester that is the ethyl ester of 4-chloro-2-(methylsulfanyl)hexahydropyrimidine-5-carboxylic acid.

A member of the class of carbapenems that is (5R,6R)-3-{[(E)-2-aminoethenyl]sulfanyl}-6-[(1S)-1-hydroxyethyl]-7-oxo-1-azabicyclo[3.2.0]hept-2-ene-2-carboxylic acid in which the free hydroxy and amino groups are carrying sulfo and acetyl substituents respectively.
A fatty acid methyl ester that is the methyl ester of any icosapentaenoic acid.
A cinnamate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of ferulic acid with one of the hydroxy groups of tartaric acid.
A glucosylglycerol consisting of a D-glucosyl residue attached at position 1 of glycerol via a glycosidic bond.
A beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1<->1')-N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group specified is tetradecanoyl.
A fatty acid ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of linoleic acid with the hydroxy group of propanol.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 36 carbons and 3 double bonds.
A 2-hydroxyphenylalanine that has L-configuration.
A phenylalanine derivative that is phenylalanine carrying a hydroxy substituent at position 2 on the benzene ring.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 38 carbons and 3 double bonds.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 40 carbons and 6 double bonds.
A 2-hydroxyphenylalanine that has D-configuration.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 25 carbons and are fully saturated.
An aryl phosphate resulting from the formal condensation of phosphoric acid with 1 mol eq. of 2-naphthol. It is a substrate for phosphatase.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 31 carbons and 1 double bond.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 37 carbons and 4 double bonds.
A phosphonic ester in which at least one of the esterifying groups is aromatic.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 43 carbons and 6 double bonds.
An aryl phosphate resulting from the formal condensation of phosphonic acid with 1 mol eq. of phenol
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 25 carbons in total with no double bonds.
An aryl phosphate resulting from the formal condensation of phosphonic acid with 1 mol eq. each of phenol and 4-nitrophenol.
An L-tyrosine derivative that is the ethyl ester of N-benzoyltyrosine.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the two phosphatidyl acyl groups contain a total of 43 carbons and 6 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 38 carbons in total with 7 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 40 carbons in total with 7 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 40 carbons in total with 8 double bonds.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of D- and L-N-benzoylphenylalanine 2-naphthylamide.
A member of the class of N-(2-naphthyl)carboxamides that is N-(naphthalen-2-yl)-3-phenylpropanamide in which one of the hydrogens at position 2 has been replaced by a benzamido group.

An N-{1-[(naphthalen-2-yl)amino]-1-oxo-3-phenylpropan-2-yl}benzamide that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-benzoyl-L-phenylalanine with the amino group of 2-aminonaphthalene.

An N-{1-[(naphthalen-2-yl)amino]-1-oxo-3-phenylpropan-2-yl}benzamide that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of N-benzoyl-D-phenylalanine with the amino group of 2-aminonaphthalene.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 20 carbons in total with 5 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 37 carbons in total with 4 double bonds.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of D- and L-N-benzoylarginine 2-naphthylamide.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 43 carbons in total with 6 double bonds.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 12 with zero double bonds.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 16 with zero double bonds.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 22 with zero double bonds.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 24 with zero double bonds.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons contained in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 24 with 1 double bond.
